WEBVTT

00:03.266 --> 00:06.832
The New Testament gospel of John.

00:08.134 --> 00:12.341
What I call your attention is 60 through verse 69.

00:13.804 --> 00:16.448
John chapter 6 verse 69.

00:17.911 --> 00:24.081
John chapter 6 verses 62 verse 69.

00:24.562 --> 00:29.170
I'm reading from the New King James Version of Scripture.

00:30.210 --> 00:36.960
Bible says, therefore many of his disciples, when they heard this said, this is a hard saying.

00:37.021 --> 00:39.484
Who can understand it?

00:41.207 --> 00:48.118
When Jesus knew in himself that his disciples complained about this, he said to them, does this offend you?

00:49.219 --> 00:55.669
What then, if you should see the son of man ascend where he was before?

00:56.811 --> 00:58.674
It is the spirit who gives life.

00:59.458 --> 01:01.340
The flesh profits nothing.

01:01.360 --> 01:10.631
The words that I speak to you are spirit and they are life, but they are some of you who do not believe.

01:11.632 --> 01:18.980
For Jesus knew from the beginning who they were who did not believe and who would betray him.

01:20.582 --> 01:27.410
And he said, therefore, I have said to you that no one can come to me unless it has been granted

01:27.842 --> 01:29.444
to him by my father.

01:30.566 --> 01:36.915
From that time, many of his disciples went back and walked with him no more.

01:37.996 --> 01:42.763
Then Jesus said to the 12, do you also want to go away?

01:42.823 --> 01:48.090
But Simon Peter answered him, Lord, to whom shall we go?

01:49.733 --> 01:52.376
You have the words of eternal life.

01:53.698 --> 01:56.402
Also, we have come to believe and know

01:56.834 --> 02:02.262
that you are the Christ, the son of the living God.

02:03.264 --> 02:03.644
Amen.

02:05.267 --> 02:13.219
Watch chapel on this last Sunday in the month of January as we celebrate victory Sunday in the life of watch chapel.

02:14.260 --> 02:21.792
I want to preach as you shall pray for and with me from the topic, sticking with Jesus.

02:22.933 --> 02:24.996
Sticking with Jesus.

02:25.036 --> 02:26.098
Look at your neighbor.

02:26.338 --> 02:34.068
smile, say neighbor, don't turn your back on Jesus, but stick with Jesus.

02:34.929 --> 02:35.349
Amen.

02:36.811 --> 02:41.297
Lord, we thank you for this opportunity to proclaim the good news of Jesus Christ.

02:42.178 --> 02:49.467
I pray now that Holy Spirit have your way in the life of every hero of this word.

02:50.248 --> 02:55.154
I pray God that this word falls on good fertile ground.

02:55.906 --> 03:10.080
Pray God that we don't turn back, we don't drift, we don't become reprobate, we don't become backsliders, that we don't stop following you, but pray God that we stick with you.

03:11.181 --> 03:20.670
Bless now, in Jesus' name, the people of God said, amen, amen, amen.

03:22.412 --> 03:24.274
Lord, bless your word, amen.

03:25.698 --> 03:29.123
Sticking with Jesus.

03:31.586 --> 03:36.733
For all of us, life is full of decisions.

03:38.636 --> 03:50.512
I can't speak for everybody individually, but it seems like every day throughout the day we are making one decision after another.

03:51.994 --> 03:54.738
If it's not a decision about one thing,

03:55.266 --> 03:58.670
then we are making a decision about something else.

03:59.951 --> 04:13.286
If it's not a decision on what we're going to buy to prepare for inclement weather, then we are making a decision to prepare for Valentine's Day that is right around the corner.

04:14.747 --> 04:24.658
If it's not a decision about exploring Bitcoin, then we are making a decision to explore cryptocurrency.

04:25.858 --> 04:39.778
If it's not a decision on what new series we're going to binge watch on Netflix, then it is a decision about what book or new book we are going to read.

04:41.280 --> 04:54.098
If it's not a decision about something we know we need to quit, then it's a decision about something we know we need to start afresh and anew.

04:55.170 --> 05:11.497
If it's not a decision about where we are going to travel, when the sun comes out and days are longer, then it's a decision about how we are going to explore what we have neglected throughout the triangle.

05:13.059 --> 05:18.007
If we're not making one decision, then we are making another decision.

05:19.169 --> 05:22.034
According to this New Testament narrative,

05:23.010 --> 05:37.146
The people of God, the 12 in particular, are making a courageous, consecrated, committed decision to stick with Jesus.

05:38.928 --> 05:51.922
If you read the entirety of John chapter six, we discover that Jesus has become increasingly popular as Jesus has fed the 5,000

05:52.258 --> 06:03.914
Men, not including women and children, as Jesus has walked on water, it seems like everybody has become attracted to Jesus.

06:04.955 --> 06:11.244
People are attracted to Jesus because of God using him as a miracle worker.

06:12.726 --> 06:21.938
Yet as we make our way towards the middle of the text, Jesus introduces himself as the bread of life.

06:23.074 --> 06:29.002
He goes from being a miracle worker to introducing himself as the bread of life.

06:30.544 --> 06:38.295
As Jesus introduces himself as the bread of life, the followers are confused concerning his identity.

06:39.096 --> 06:43.081
They raised the question, isn't this Mary's son?

06:43.141 --> 06:46.666
Isn't this Joseph's stepson?

06:46.686 --> 06:52.434
Isn't this the boy who was raised and he's talking about he has come from heaven?

06:52.834 --> 06:54.917
And he is the bread of life.

06:56.178 --> 07:04.990
Moreover, Jesus doubles down and reintroduces himself and reaffirms his identity as the bread of life.

07:05.871 --> 07:15.845
Jesus talks about if you want to really experience God, you have to eat of the bread that I am offering.

07:17.747 --> 07:19.730
The disciples are confused.

07:20.546 --> 07:25.552
because this is, according to the language, a hard saying.

07:26.994 --> 07:38.848
Jesus knows who believes and who does not believe in the text says that the masses of people follow him no more.

07:40.110 --> 07:50.162
They stop following Jesus with the same verb, excitement, enthusiasm, because Jesus communicated

07:50.466 --> 08:03.303
a hard saying about him being the bread of life and him and it being necessary for them to embrace him as the bread of life.

08:04.906 --> 08:19.986
And while the masses of people are leaving, the text says that the 12 have decided not to leave, but they are sticking with Jesus.

08:20.834 --> 08:41.396
And on this Victory Sunday watch chapel, I've come by here to encourage every believer, every friend, every disciple, every seeker, every would-be disciple, not to conform to the crowd, but to make up your mind to stick with Jesus.

08:42.938 --> 08:46.642
Despite who walks away, we ought to stick with Jesus.

08:47.523 --> 08:50.226
Despite who has stopped coming to church,

08:50.786 --> 08:52.568
We ought to stick with Jesus.

08:53.429 --> 08:59.117
Despite what they say about you, worshiping God in spirit and in truth.

08:59.758 --> 09:01.981
You ought to stick with Jesus.

09:03.202 --> 09:12.654
There are many people who have gone away, who are now M-I-A, who are church dropouts.

09:13.496 --> 09:18.482
Once upon a time, they were here praising God in spirit and in truth.

09:19.010 --> 09:37.975
Once upon a time, they couldn't wait till the doors of the church were open, but somewhere along the journey, frustration, disappointment, rearrange priorities, decisions, not to stick with Jesus, but to fall away.

09:39.036 --> 09:42.200
But let not not be said about you and I.

09:43.642 --> 09:46.706
On this victory Sunday, we ought to double down.

09:47.586 --> 09:48.848
We ought to sign up again.

09:48.888 --> 09:51.112
We ought to renew our commitment.

09:51.773 --> 09:53.215
We ought to make up in our mind.

09:53.335 --> 09:54.958
I'm not going to fall away.

09:55.098 --> 09:56.620
I'm not going to shrink back.

09:57.141 --> 10:01.668
I'm not going to backslide, but I'm going to stick with Jesus.

10:02.910 --> 10:09.681
And watch that, but I'm encouraging every believer to stick with Jesus.

10:09.701 --> 10:15.730
If the 12th could stick with Jesus, you and I ought to stick with Jesus.

10:16.450 --> 10:23.160
Watch that book, the 12 stick with Jesus because they possess something called endurance.

10:25.324 --> 10:32.154
If you're going to be a follower of the Lord Jesus Christ, every day will not be Sunday.

10:32.194 --> 10:35.719
Everybody will not be a skip rope buddy.

10:35.740 --> 10:45.234
Everybody will not be in your proverbial amen corner, but you and I must embrace the personal quality

10:45.602 --> 10:49.088
virtue and value of endurance.

10:50.169 --> 10:52.052
I don't know what you want to call it.

10:52.112 --> 10:54.516
You can call it grit.

10:54.536 --> 10:56.980
You can call it intestinal fortitude.

10:57.421 --> 10:59.184
You can call it tenacity.

10:59.745 --> 11:01.547
You can call it perseverance.

11:02.148 --> 11:10.642
But whatever synonym you want to use, if you're going to stick with Jesus, you need endurance.

11:12.194 --> 11:34.902
Days will be dark, sometimes friends will be few, haters will be numerous, mockers will mock, people will ridicule, sayings will be hard, yet with endurance we can see it through and we can stick with Jesus.

11:36.043 --> 11:38.546
I don't know who I'm talking to on this Sunday morning.

11:39.682 --> 11:45.389
But if you've ever achieved anything in life, it did not come easy.

11:46.550 --> 11:51.416
If you've been married for more than a decade, it was not easy.

11:52.297 --> 11:58.885
If you've graduated from some institution of higher learning, it was not always easy.

11:59.605 --> 12:06.994
If you have climbed the corporate ladder and now have a corner office, it has not been easy.

12:07.618 --> 12:13.484
If you overcame some health issue, it has not always been easy.

12:14.225 --> 12:20.391
But if you look back over the journey of your life, it has required endurance.

12:22.033 --> 12:30.502
And following Jesus as a disciple of the Lord Jesus Christ requires endurance.

12:31.543 --> 12:34.866
If we're going to stick and stay with Jesus,

12:35.394 --> 12:37.377
We have to endure haters.

12:37.497 --> 12:39.120
We have to endure mockers.

12:39.660 --> 12:42.184
We have to endure dry seasons.

12:42.645 --> 12:44.648
We have to endure difficulty.

12:45.149 --> 12:47.472
We have to endure disillusionment.

12:47.893 --> 12:54.383
We have to endure seasons where we wonder why God is allowing what God has allowed.

12:54.423 --> 13:00.512
Yet if we're going to stick with Jesus, we need endurance.

13:02.635 --> 13:04.338
In 1955,

13:05.634 --> 13:09.859
The modern day civil rights movement launched in Montgomery, Alabama.

13:11.140 --> 13:25.918
And our mothers and fathers spent over one year boycotting the public bus system in Montgomery, Alabama.

13:25.938 --> 13:33.266
Not just in the summertime, not just in the fall, but in the winter, in the spring,

13:33.922 --> 13:46.903
They made up their mind, they were going to endure so they could enjoy the rights they deserved as citizens of these United States of America.

13:47.765 --> 14:00.946
And after more than a year, the civil rights movement was blessed with full occupancy on buses in Montgomery

14:01.602 --> 14:05.348
because our mothers and fathers endured.

14:07.391 --> 14:11.778
Sticking with Jesus requires endurance.

14:13.040 --> 14:15.845
It just doesn't require endurance, watch chapel.

14:16.726 --> 14:20.232
Sticking with Jesus requires encouragement.

14:21.955 --> 14:29.106
Text says that the masses have left, but everybody didn't leave.

14:29.922 --> 14:35.547
The 12 made up in their mind, they were going to stick with Jesus.

14:36.548 --> 14:52.623
And in the midst of sticking with Jesus in my sanctified imagination, watch chapel, the 12 became a mutual encouragement society where they made up their mind.

14:52.703 --> 14:54.105
We're not going to leave.

14:54.785 --> 14:59.730
We're not going to desert him, but we are going to stick with Jesus.

15:00.066 --> 15:07.717
And in the midst of sticking with Jesus, they encouraged one another on the journey.

15:09.300 --> 15:14.127
Inevitably, there had to be somebody who was thinking about leaving with the crowd.

15:14.988 --> 15:16.070
I don't know who it was.

15:16.130 --> 15:20.716
It may have been James and John, may have been Bartholomew, may have been Simon.

15:21.417 --> 15:23.160
Judas was already out of pocket.

15:23.861 --> 15:29.970
We don't know who it was exactly, but Peter declares, where shall we go?

15:30.882 --> 15:33.544
You have the words of eternal life.

15:34.646 --> 15:42.453
And I believe that these brothers encouraged one another to stick with Jesus.

15:43.834 --> 15:50.781
There's some believer who hears this sermon right now, who's trying to live the Christian life all by yourself.

15:51.822 --> 15:53.964
My brother, my sister, none of us live.

15:54.564 --> 15:57.847
They're victorious, triumphant Christian life by ourselves.

15:58.848 --> 16:00.850
In the words of the song, I need you.

16:01.474 --> 16:02.576
You need me.

16:03.597 --> 16:06.302
We need one another.

16:07.684 --> 16:16.959
And if we're going to stick with Jesus, we have to give encouragement, but also be willing to embrace encouragement.

16:18.160 --> 16:22.087
When you want to quit, learn how to encourage yourself.

16:23.068 --> 16:29.298
When somebody wants to quit, learn to be a sanctified cheerleader in their life.

16:30.018 --> 16:35.945
When somebody stops coming to church, reach out to them and encourage them to get back in the fold.

16:37.247 --> 16:50.804
When somebody is not present the way they used to be, encourage them, all of us need encouragement from the choir stand to the parking lot, from the pool pit to deacons row.

16:51.705 --> 16:59.314
Every believer needs encouragement and none of us stick and stay without

16:59.650 --> 17:00.951
in encouragement.

17:02.353 --> 17:07.558
How can God use you as an encourager in the life of somebody else?

17:08.579 --> 17:15.746
How can God use you to encourage somebody to live to their best, to the glory of God?

17:16.607 --> 17:25.836
If we're going to stick with Jesus, we need to embrace encouragement and we need to give encouragement.

17:26.736 --> 17:28.338
They stick with Jesus.

17:29.570 --> 17:30.951
because of encouragement.

17:32.093 --> 17:41.223
They stick with Jesus because of endurance, but they stick with Jesus because of expectancy.

17:43.145 --> 17:51.274
These are the 12 disciples who have walked and talked with Jesus along the journey.

17:52.975 --> 17:59.122
James and John, fishermen, left their profitable fishing business

17:59.522 --> 18:08.331
So they could follow Jesus, Levi, Matthew, leaves the tax collectors booth so he could follow Jesus.

18:09.392 --> 18:19.122
The others, amen, leave their vocations, their professions so they can follow Jesus.

18:19.142 --> 18:26.930
In John chapter two, they encounter a miracle where Jesus turns water into wine.

18:27.810 --> 18:34.460
And the text says, after he turns water into wine, they believed in him.

18:34.480 --> 18:43.854
In other sense, that first miracle, these men have lived with a sense of expectancy.

18:45.036 --> 18:49.783
Jesus has done what Jesus said he was going to do.

18:50.604 --> 18:51.926
He has healed the sick.

18:51.947 --> 18:53.609
He has raised the dead.

18:53.649 --> 18:56.914
He has turned water into wine.

18:57.346 --> 19:02.612
